olive oil
1 beetroot
1 carrot
1 parsnip
1 packet couscous
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 packet Currants
¾ cup boiling water
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
2 packet Pork Loin Steaks
drizzle honey
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Mint

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Boil the kettle. Cut beetroot into 1cm chunks. Cut parsnip and carrot into bite-size chunks.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat.
• Roast until golden, 20-25 minutes.

• Place couscous, vegetable stock powder and currants stock in a medium heatproof bowl.
• Add the boiling water (see ingredients) and stir to combine.
• Immediately cover with a plate and leave for 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork and set aside.

• In a medium bowl, combine chermoula spice blend, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Add pork loin steaks and turn to coat (cook in batches if required).
• Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook pork until cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side (depending on thickness).
• Remove pan from heat and add a drizzle of honey, turn to coat and transfer to a plate. Cover to rest for 5 minutes.

• When veggies are done, add to couscous and stir to combine.
• Slice chermoula pork.
• Divide roast veggie couscous, and pork between bowls.
• Drizzle with Greek-style yoghurt. Tear over mint. Enjoy!